{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8be95cbe-faf5-4cc0-8a97-a4017c39e961","content":"Here's the correct skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four report the reason in test results so you can track why tests were skipped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a9393ff8-dee8-4037-a914-10c8a62989a7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":221,"requestId":"3409:3BFDE:C16F16:E113E1:69F3FF13"},"id":"2a60344c-2f38-47c0-83bb-a6f5d0ca86a6","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:17:13.399Z","parentId":"a036b5bf-2434-49f5-ab94-d2fcd5a1774d"}
